fields.description:
The Dockerized BenTen should be tested on perf and the results  are compiled and signed off.

As  a consumer of BenTen service,
when BenTen apis are called in perf env
then dockerized BenTen service should be able to support the load.

Notes :
1. Deploy on Perf and run smoke perf.
2.   Perf Tetesting.

Tetest should include ( 1 container test : max TPM – 2 hr, then extrapolate and run for 12 hrs , test memory settings configuration  )

Conditions of Satisfaction:
1.  Performance of the service running on Docker matches that of the service running on VM (within reason)

Notes : BenTen Dockerization Performance Matches BenTen VM Performance

items.toString: Recently we release wms onto production with threat remediation changes and ran encryption script. We encountered an issue with properties not getting decrypted for few jobs. On RCA, we found the encryption script has issue. The properties of one job got updated to another job.

2. All the data with sensitive fields should be encrypted in the production for wms.
